==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snell
<hw>Snell</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>snell</ets>;
akin to D. <ets>snel</ets>, G. <ets>schnell</ets>, OHG. <ets>snel</ets>,
Icel. <ets>snjallr</ets> valiant.]</ety> <def>Active; brisk; nimble;
quick; sharp.</def> <mark>[Archaic or Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That horny-handed, <qex>snell</qex>, peremptory little man.</q>
<rj><qau>Dr. J. Brown.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snell</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Snell
<hw>Snell</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A short line of horsehair, gut, etc.,
by which a fishhook is attached to a longer line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snet</ent>⟦br⟧
